I"‘<h2 id="fuse-ext2">Fuse-ext2</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Install dependencies:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>brew tap homebrew/fuse
brew <span class="nb">install </span>Caskroom/cask/osxfuse
brew <span class="nb">install </span>e2fsprogs m4 automake autoconf libtool
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Clone repository:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git clone <span class="nt">--depth</span><span class="o">=</span>1 https://github.com/alperakcan/fuse-ext2.git
<span class="nb">cd </span>fuse-ext2
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Missing <em>XCode</em> workaround (optional):
If <em>XCode</em> is not installed, the following error will be thrown:
    <blockquote>
      <p>xcode-select: error: tool â€˜xcodebuildâ€™ requires Xcode, but active developer directory â€˜/Library/Developer/CommandLineToolsâ€™ is a command line tools instance</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>Since <em>XCode</em> is actually not required for building <code class="highlighter-rouge">fuse-ext2</code>, this little workaround makes the error go away:</p>
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">ln</span> <span class="nt">-s</span> /usr/bin/true /usr/local/bin/xcodebuild
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Build &amp; Install:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>./autogen.sh
<span class="nv">CFLAGS</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"-idirafter/</span><span class="si">$(</span>brew <span class="nt">--prefix</span> e2fsprogs<span class="si">)</span><span class="s2">/include -idirafter/usr/local/include/osxfuse"</span> <span class="nv">LDFLAGS</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"-L</span><span class="si">$(</span>brew <span class="nt">--prefix</span> e2fsprogs<span class="si">)</span><span class="s2">/lib"</span>  ./configure
make
<span class="nb">sudo </span>make <span class="nb">install</span>
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Enable write access:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo sed</span> <span class="nt">-e</span> <span class="s1">'s/OPTIONS="local,allow_other"/OPTIONS="local,allow_other,rw+"/'</span> <span class="nt">-i</span>.orig /Library/Filesystems/fuse-ext2.fs/fuse-ext2.util
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Remove the <em>XCode</em> workaround symlink (optional):
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">rm</span> /usr/local/bin/xcodebuild
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2 id="ext4fuse">Ext4fuse</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Install <code class="highlighter-rouge">ext4fuse</code>
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>brew <span class="nb">install </span>ext4fuse
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Add current user to <em>operator</em> group:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>dscl <span class="nb">.</span> append /Groups/operator GroupMembership <span class="sb">`</span><span class="nb">whoami</span><span class="sb">`</span>
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2 id="mount-ext4-disk">Mount Ext4 Disk</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Show available disks:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>diskutil list
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Unmount Disk:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>diskutil unmountDisk /dev/disk2
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Mount partition:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">mkdir </span>mnt
<span class="nb">sudo </span>fuse-ext2 /dev/disk2s2 mnt <span class="nt">-o</span> rw+
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Unmount partition:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>umount mnt
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

